&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Nightshift slowly skulks into view with his tail held low.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Oh slag, there goes my cover.  Oh well at least we werent attacked.
&gt; Better play along with her.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; He follows the insectile queen with a twitch of his tail.  His whiskers
&gt; twitch with anxiety.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Um, if ya don&#39;t mind me ask&#39;n, why did ya have the tower fire at us?  This
&gt; is Maximal territory. &quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

Actually the insectile queen herself is no where in sight. All that
can be seen are the two troopers at the door. NIGHTSHIFT&#39;s sole
connection to the queen is the voice coming over the radio.

The queen&#39;s voice chuckled, &quot;Maximal, Predacon, you think that your
petty names mean anything?&quot; Her voice is humorous and yet tired as it
comes over the radio. &quot;Come to me.&quot; She said again.

Meanwhile the two troopers lead NIGHTSHIFT and BATSCOUT to the main
lift and step inside, the lift that would lead towards the very top of
CRYONOSIS.

There was a short buzzing sound on NIGHTSHIFT&#39;s radio. At the same
time BATSCOUT froze for a moment, &quot;Antonymous mode active.&quot; he said
quietly.

It would seem that radio communication had been cut off to the
outside. From here on NIGHTSHIFT and BATSCOUT would be on their own.

&quot;Cryonosis does my bidding now.&quot; The queen&#39;s voice said ominously.
&quot;And I have a special mission for it.&quot; Her voice had an ominous sound
to it.

